                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>seems to be your guiding star<add>?</add> in all of<lb/> your\n                                        productions. It becomes your character<lb/> and will keep\n                                        you elevated as long as it<lb/> is exercised.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">With many wishes for your<lb/> welfare</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">I remain your obt. st.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Isaac N. Cardilo</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>N. B. I perceive that you have<lb/> introduced the word (wrangle)\n                                        in <persName>Mr.<lb/> Eckman's</persName> letter under the\n                                        idea. I<lb/> suppose, that it was an omission of<lb/>\n                                        mine—but the original contained as-<lb/>-terisks as I sent\n                                        it to you—altho'<lb/> the context would <add>?</add> the\n                                        introduction of<lb/> the world “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >wrangle</hi>.”</p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3445hz65/canvas/p2"
